The paper deals with the computational complexity of the Maximum Common Induced Subgraph problem, which is a graph isomorphism problem. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The paper also discusses the parameterized complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Computational Geometry (cs.CG) categories. Finally, the paper proposes algorithms and lower bounds, which indicates that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category.
